  "summary": "The Long Play Trail Run is a rhythmic ultramarathon set in the Croom Tract of Florida's Withlacoochee State Forest, known for its rare single-loop course through lush cypress swamps and pine forests. This event centers around a musical 'Long Play' theme, offering a flagship distance of 33.3 miles as a clever tribute to the 33 1/3 RPM of classic vinyl records.",
  "uniqueFeatures": [
    "Vinyl Record Finishers' Awards: Every runner who completes the course receives an actual vinyl record as a unique trophy, keeping with the race's 'Long Play' musical theme.",
    "33.3-Mile Single Loop: Unlike many ultramarathons that use multiple laps, this race features a continuous 33.3-mile loop that takes runners deep into seldom-traveled sections of the state forest.",
    "Wild Hog Topography: The terrain presents natural obstacles including 'sugary sand' and uneven ground churned up by the local wild hog population, creating a technically challenging surface."
